# SuperGit Refresh & Async Coordination

Lessons from fetch/prune/reload performance debugging. Read before changing `extension.ts`, `App.tsx` commit loading, or remotes cache.

## Managed refresh (`extension.ts`)

Any path that runs slow ref-mutating Git (`fetch --all --prune`, push, pull, prune-stale, title-bar Refresh) must:

1. Call `beginManagedRefresh(scope)` **before** the slow command (not after success).
2. Clear pending repo-watcher debounce timers on start.
3. Skip repo-change events **immediately** when guard is active (not only inside the 400ms callback).
4. Call `endManagedRefresh(generation)` only after fetch + reload finish; clear flag via generation-matched delayed settle.

**Never** use a shared boolean + unconditional `setTimeout(..., 1500)` to clear suppression — overlapping operations (e.g. prune-stale then Refresh) will clear each other's guards mid-fetch.

## In-flight coalescing

| Operation | Pattern |
|-----------|---------|
| `loadInitialData` | Dedupe in-flight promise; log `coalesced with in-flight load` |
| `enrichRemoteDefaultsInBackground` | Check inflight map **before** bumping generation; key = `root + sorted remote names` |
| Apply enriched remotes | Post only when `key === latestEnrichRemoteDefaultsKey` (handles A→B→A coalesce edge) |
| `loadBranchHistory` | Bump `branchHistoryLoadGeneration` on start; post data and clear `branch-history` loading only when `generation === branchHistoryLoadGeneration` (overlapping tab entry + post-action reload) |

Do **not** increment enrichment generation on coalesced return — that skips valid in-flight results.

## Cache invalidation

Call `invalidateRemoteDataCaches(root)` (clears `clearRemotesCache` + `clearRemoteDefaultBranchCache`) on:

- Successful manual refresh fetch
- Successful branch actions
- Repo-watcher debounced reload (external `git remote` add/remove, fetch/prune, remote HEAD changes)

Without default-branch cache invalidation, default badges and delete-default-remote guards can stay stale after fetch/prune or remote HEAD updates.

**Stale upstream cleanup:** `unsetStaleUpstreamLinks()` runs only from explicit **Prune Stale** (confirmed action), not title-bar Refresh. Abort cleanup when `refs/remotes/` for-each-ref fails — never treat a failed listing as “no refs exist.”

**Post-action reload:** `fetch` and `prune-stale` must call `loadCommits` (remote refs on graph). `delete-remote` must reload branches, remotes, and commits.

**Branch history after actions:** `runBranchAction` must **not** unconditionally call `loadBranchHistory` — it is expensive (~100+ Git commands). Gate with `shouldReloadBranchHistoryAfterAction(actionTab, currentTab)` in `src/extension/refreshPolicy.ts`: reload when **either** the click-time `activeTab` snapshot **or** host `activeWebviewTab` (from `tab-changed`) is `"history"`. This avoids stale History after a mid-action tab switch. Webview posts `tab-changed` via a single `useEffect([tab])`; `loadBranches` + `loadRemotes` may run in parallel. Switching to History tab still triggers `request-branch-history` lazily.

## Webview commit requests (`App.tsx`)

Initial `ready` → host `loadInitialData` already loads commits. Avoid duplicate `request-commits`.

**Do not** use one-shot skip flags cleared inside a `useEffect` — if deps unchanged (e.g. `pagination.page` stays 0), the flag is never consumed and the **first real user change is swallowed**.

**Use query-key matching:**

- `satisfiedCommitQueryKey` = JSON of `{ dateRange, page, searchText, scope }` last satisfied by host
- Update on every `commits-data` (use refs for current filters in the message listener)
- Post `request-commits` only when current query key ≠ `satisfiedCommitQueryKey`

## Log verification (count, do not vibe-check)

Before claiming a refresh fix, grep the latest `supergit.log`:

| Invariant | One manual Refresh |
|-----------|-------------------|
| `managed refresh start` | 1 |
| `fetch --all --prune` | 1 start, 1 complete |
| `loadInitialData start` | 1 after fetch (not during) |
| `refreshing after repository change` | 0 mid-fetch |
| `repository change skipped; managed refresh already running` | may be >0 during fetch |

Also test **overlap**: Prune Stale immediately followed by title-bar Refresh.

## Static review triggers

Re-read diffs that introduce:

- `setTimeout` clearing shared suppression/coalescing state
- Message handler sets a ref flag; effect clears it (verify effect always runs when flag is set)
- Global single promise for enrichment without per-key + latest-key apply guard

Network-bound `fetch --all --prune` (~5s) is expected; the win is eliminating **extra** full reloads during fetch. Refresh button: disabled + tooltip while `loading` scope `all`.
